@body
Plans of the highest priority are listed first.
<p>
<ul>
<li>Make a common document system for usage, help, man and info.
<li>Pickup definitions of data type, macro with no argument, 
enum name, enum value, union name and struct name. Finally, remove GSYMS.
<li>Write plugged-in parser writer's guide.
<li>Support other developing environment.
	<ul>
	<li><a href=http://www.delorie.com/djgpp/>DJGPP</a>
	</ul>
<li>Include external parsers.<br>
	I would like to include parsers which belong to the following systems:
        <ul>
        <li><a href=http://www.gedanken.demon.co.uk/cxref/>Cxref</a>
        <li><a href=http://sources.redhat.com/sourcenav/>Source-Navigator</a>
        </ul>
<li>Rewrite online manual with man format. (Currently mandoc format.)
<li>Support other editors.
	<ul>
	<li>nvi-1.81
	</ul>
<li>Support of other languages.<br>
        <ul>
	<li>PHP
        <li>Scheme
        <li>Texinfo
        <li>LaTeX
	<li>Lex
        </ul>
<li>Visual interface with GUI.
<li>Ttags(1) command.<br>
        Ttags(1) is similar to htags(1) but makes TeX source for a book
        instead of hypertext.
</ul>
Any contributions are appreciated.
Please see <a href=contribute.html>contribution</a>.
